  <h2>Test the trip before choosing</h2>
  <p>Before buying laundry hampers, baskets or sorters, check:</p>
  <ul class="feature-list">
    <li>What problem is the basket solving?</li>
    <li>Do I need one basket or several?</li>
    <li>Have I measured the floor space?</li>
    <li>Will it block the washing machine, dryer, tub or walkway?</li>
    <li>Is it easy to carry when full?</li>
    <li>Does it need ventilation for damp items?</li>
    <li>Does the household actually sort washing before laundry day?</li>
    <li>Does it suit bedrooms, bathrooms or the laundry?</li>
    <li>Is clean laundry being handled separately?</li>
    <li>Is it suitable for a rental or small space?</li>
    <li>Is it easy to clean?</li>
    <li>Would changing the routine solve the issue first?</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Laundry basket storage works best when it matches the way the household actually handles
    washing.
  </p>
  <p>
    Sort the routine first, measure the space, and choose baskets that make washing easier
    to collect, carry, separate and put away.
  </p>

